brb_core/synthetic_data.py

Purpose:
Simulates realistic IAM data so the system can be developed and tested without production access.

What it does:

Generates users under supervisors

Assigns job codes, departments, assignment types

Ensures some roles are common (signal) and some are random (noise)

Mimics real-world IAM distributions using randomness

Why it exists:
To validate logic, thresholds, and edge cases before integrating real HR / SailPoint data.

ğŸ“ brb_core/bundling.py

Purpose:
Identifies Business Role candidates using deterministic logic.

What it does:

Groups users by org context (e.g., supervisor + job code)

Finds frequent pairs and triples of activity roles

Applies thresholds:

minimum group size

minimum role support

minimum bundle support

Tags suggestions (Birthright / Job-Based / Department)

Key idea:
â€œIf a set of roles appears together for most users in a cohort, itâ€™s a business role candidate.â€

ğŸ“ brb_core/metrics.py

Purpose:
Provides role usage intelligence (Access Ratio Evaluator).

What it does:

Calculates role coverage (% of users with a role)

Identifies unused / low-use roles

Builds per-user access summaries

Detects overlapping roles using Jaccard similarity

Why it matters:
Supports governance, cleanup, audits, and explains why roles exist.

ğŸ“ brb_core/sod_rules.py

Purpose:
Defines Segregation of Duties (SoD) policy framework.

What it does:

Stores SoD conflict rules with severity (LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH)

Detects conflicts in a proposed role set

Applies policy:

blocks HIGH severity

warns on MEDIUM / LOW

Design choice:
Rule-based + severity-aware â†’ audit-friendly and extensible later.

ğŸ“ brb_core/new_joiner.py

Purpose:
Recommends access for new joiners in a controlled, explainable way.

What it does:

Builds a cohort (job code + supervisor/department)

Recommends roles used by most users in that cohort

Applies SoD policy and removes high-risk roles

Outputs coverage %, reasons, and SoD details

Key point:
This is recommendation, not auto-provisioning.

ğŸ“ brb_core/run_local.py

Purpose:
Local orchestration layer (Phase 1 pipeline runner).

What it does:

Generates synthetic IAM data

Runs bundling engine

Runs metrics + overlap analysis

Runs new joiner recommendation

Exports all outputs to CSV

Why itâ€™s important:
Acts as the backbone that later becomes:

Lambda / ECS job

API backend

MLOps pipeline entry point

